The paper discusses a method for generating high-quality and diverse question-answer pairs from unstructured text corpus using neural question generators. This involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques, which are commonly associated with the sub-categories of arXiv CS such as Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely ones for this paper.
